   NATIONAL MEDIA Corp. (Philadelphia) -- Donald J. McDonald
Jr., 37 years old, was elected president of this direct
marketing services concern. He succeeds John Sgarlat, who
resigned in April 1989. No one has been named to fill Mr.
McDonald's former post as executive vice president. Mr.
McDonald retains his position as chief operating officer. The
company said it added six new board members, expanding the
panel to nine members. The new directors are Mr. McDonald,
Anthony Pironti, Nancy M. Langston, Ewin Ducat, David Baxter
and Brian McAdams.
